  "source": "Lemma:\n. \"Lemma 4.35\"\ngiven:\n. C is \\set\nwhere:\n. forAll: A, B is \\set\n  where:\n  . A \"in\" C\n  . B \"in\" C\n  then:\n  . anyOf:\n    . A \\.continuation.of./ B\n    . B \\.continuation.of./ A\nthen:\n. exists: U is \\set\n  suchThat:\n  . \\well.ordered{U}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Let $C$ be a chain with respect to continuation and $U = \\bigcup_{D \\in C} D$. Then there is a unique well ordering of $U$ making $U$ a continuation of each element of $C$ distinct from $U$. This lets one build a well ordered set from a chain of initial segments.\"\nId: \"04a1fede-4f52-4915-ad37-848cce1f674c\"",
